metadata.name: Clouds over the Mountains #170
metadata.description:
“I'd go as far as the end of a stream or fountain, 
And sit and gaze on cloud rising over the mountain.” 
— Wang Wei (Tang dynasty)

「行到水窮處，坐看雲起時。」
—— 唐·王維

This artwork is inspired by the poem above, and creates a view to “gaze on cloud rising over the mountain”. 
This is also a tribute to the traditional Chinese landscape painting. 

☁️☁️☁️☁️
⛰️⛰️⛰️⛰️

It takes time to generate. Run on a computer for better experience. 
Student of @Newyellow. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Con(text)ual #79
metadata.description:
Con(text)ual is a generative painting made from ASCII characters confined into shapes. Shapes are randomly drawn onto the canvas, then filled with individual characters from a character array. The density of characters is dependent upon the size of the shape, creating some transparencies and an organic feel to each shape.

I've long been interested in typography as an artform and this is an extension of my typography explorations.

There are a total of 10 color pallets. The number of shapes on each canvas varies from 3 to 9. The edition size was chosen based on the code, which lends itself well to a wide array of potential outcomes. Please get in touch with me if you want a larger resolution size for printing. 

I hope you enjoy the art!

Made with 100% Code and p5.js
Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Perlin Sun #34
metadata.description:
"Perlin Sun" by Marnix Keller consists of 52 pieces, one for each week of the year.

It has at it's centre, a sun consisting of two colours.  A base colour overlaid with another of Perlin noise.

There are 5 possible sun palettes:
"Strawberries and lime"
"Harvest gold"
"White heat"
"Blood orange"
"Margarita"

There are 6 possible sky palettes:
"Azure"
"Arctic twilight"
"Purple haze"
"Desert days"
"Mountain air"
"Skyfall"

There are 5 possible ground palettes:
"Green grass of home"
"Distant shores"
"Meadow mountain"
"Sandy lane"
"The north island"
            
There is the possibility of clouds and birds, but these are rare...
